related_items.title: Bilder von Mitau, Rukmann, Riga, Dorpat, Reval; 1917/18
description: 1 album (56 photographic prints) ; 33 x 26 cm. (album). | Photograph album shows general views from cities in Latvia and Estonia during World War I. Includes scenes from Riga, Jelgava (Mitau) and Rukmann near Daudzeva in Latvia and from Tallinn (Reval) and Tartu (Dorpat) in Estonia. Includes views of  churches, bridges, theaters, government buildings, streets and boulevards, town halls. Includes winter scenes and a few interior views. Also includes views of war damage of a railway bridge in Riga and scenes of a mine sweeper in Riga harbor.
